# Why this exists:
#
# l402-requests@0.1.x declares `@noble/secp256k1: ">=2.0.0"` as an
# OPTIONAL peer dependency. The actual NWC wallet code path inside that
# package calls `secp256k1.schnorr.sign(...)`, which only exists in
# @noble/secp256k1@^1.7.x — v2+ moved the schnorr submodule out to
# @noble/curves. So this repo pins @noble/secp256k1 to ^1.7.1 to
# match the API the wallet code actually uses.
#
# npm 7+ enforces optional peer-dep ranges strictly and refuses to
# install our v1.7.x pin against the upstream's v2+ declaration,
# failing the Vercel build with ERESOLVE. `legacy-peer-deps=true`
# switches npm back to the pre-7 behavior of treating peer deps as
# advisory (warn, don't fail).
#
# Remove this file once l402-requests is fixed upstream to either
# tighten its peer-dep range to ^1.7.0 or migrate its schnorr import
# to @noble/curves/secp256k1 — tracked in priority-backlog #86.
legacy-peer-deps=true
